This file marks that the project's wiki/ follows the seven-section
documentation taxonomy from ADR 0004 of agentm (amended 2026-06-11 to
converge on crickets' frame). Five sections are always present; two are
conditional:

  how-to/      — task-oriented recipes (onboarding walkthroughs live here,
                 numerically prefixed, carrying a `<!-- mode: tutorial -->`
                 hint so the gate holds them to tutorial discipline)
  reference/   — canonical lookup tables, flags, APIs
  designs/     — "Why we built X" design docs (crickets' /design skill)
  explanation/ — narrative rationale, intent, trade-offs
  decisions/   — Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)

  architecture/ — added only when a per-repo wiki/architecture.yml manifest
                  declares it
  operational/  — added only when the repo's visibility is non-public

Presence of this marker enables strict-mode `check-wiki.py` for this
project. Do not remove unless you are migrating away from the taxonomy.

See:
- wiki/README.md — the convention as it applies here.
- https://github.com/alexherrero/agentm/blob/main/wiki/decisions/0004-diataxis-documentation-spec.md
